text: Murtaza () is a rural locality (a village) in Sterlibashevsky Selsoviet, Sterlibashevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 165 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 11 km from Sterlibashevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlibashevsky District
title: Murtaza, Sterlibashevsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
